name: Starters
about: Fresh summer rolls. Choice of protein with lettuce, seasonal herbs, and vermicelli noodles rolled in fresh rice paper. Served with peanut sauce. *gf except peanut sauce - suggest nuac cham as substitute. *always declare your food allergy on the order. Fried imperial rolls. Pork or vegetarian with carrots, onions, mushrooms, and noodles rolled in wheat flour pastry and fried to a golden brown. Served with nước chấm. Wrapper contains egg. Vietnamese chicken wings. Flash fried salt & pepper chicken wings served with a spicy chili-lime dipping sauce. *gf if requested *always declare your food allergy in your order. Filled w/pork & shrimp steamed and served w/ chili oil sauce, garnished with peanuts, scallions and cilantro. Wrapper contains egg.

name: Vietnamese Classics
about: Rice noodle soup served in our aromatic bone broth garnished with scallions, sweet onion and cilantro. Served with fresh basil, bean sprouts, jalapeno, and lime. *gf *vegan option available. Rice vermicelli noodles choice of protein plated over a bed of fresh rice noodles, lettuce, cilantro, seasonal greens, pickled carrots and daikon, cucumbers, and crushed peanuts. Rice bowl choice of protein served over jasmine rice with pickled carrots and daikon, cilantro, cucumber, and topped w/a fried egg. Crispy fried pork ribs, served with jasmine rice, peanuts, thai chilis, fried shallots, fresh vietnamese herbs and side of n1/2 serving of your favorite banh mi & pho with your choice of protein for each. Available until 2:00 pm. *gf pho saigon only *always declare your food allergy on the order.

name: Sunday Menu: Dim Sum & Small Plates
about: Served Sundays, 12pm-8pm. We recommend 2-3 plates per person to share at the table (or keep to yourself!). Steamed crystal dumplings with shrimp and bamboo shoots. The signature Dim Sum specialty! Open face pork dumplings. Two fluffy steamed buns with cucumber, scallions, hoisin sauce. Choice of grilled Makrut lime chicken or marinated mushrooms. Vegetarian fried rice garnished with cilantro, scallions, and fried shallots. Option to add Lap Xuong (Chinese sausage) for $2.
